      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do men\'s multivitamins really support testosterone?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Men\'s multivitamins do not directly increase testosterone like hormone replacement therapy. However, correcting deficiencies in testosterone-supporting nutrients can optimize natural testosterone production. Zinc deficiency is directly linked to low testosterone — a study in Nutrition found that zinc supplementation in zinc-deficient men increased testosterone by 93% over 6 months. Vitamin D deficiency is associated with lower testosterone levels, and supplementation in deficient men can increase testosterone by 25%. Magnesium supplementation in athletes increased free testosterone by 24% in one study. The key: supplements optimize testosterone only if you are deficient in these nutrients.' },
