      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is the difference between men\'s and unisex multivitamins?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Men\'s multivitamins differ from unisex formulas in several ways: they typically contain zero iron (to avoid excess accumulation), higher doses of zinc and selenium (for prostate and testosterone support), higher B-vitamin doses (for energy metabolism during physical activity), lycopene (antioxidant for prostate health), and sometimes saw palmetto or other prostate-specific ingredients. They exclude or reduce nutrients that women need in higher amounts, such as iron, folate (at pregnancy-supporting doses), and calcium (at osteoporosis-prevention doses). Men\'s formulas are optimized for male-specific health priorities.' },
    },
