      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'At what age should men start taking a multivitamin?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Men of any age can benefit from a multivitamin if their diet has nutritional gaps. However, specific age-related considerations make supplementation more important over time: In their 20s-30s, men benefit from zinc, magnesium, and B vitamins for energy, fitness, and stress management. In their 40s, vitamin D and omega-3 become more important as cardiovascular risk factors increase and testosterone begins declining (~1% per year after age 30). In their 50s+, B12 absorption decreases (stomach acid declines), prostate health concerns increase (selenium, lycopene, zinc become critical), and bone density preservation requires adequate vitamin D and calcium.' },
