    <h2 id="why-mens-vitamins">What Men Actually Need From a Multivitamin</h2>

    <p>Men's nutritional priorities differ fundamentally from women's. Heart disease is the number one killer of men in the United States, making cardiovascular nutrients (omega-3, CoQ10, magnesium) critical. Testosterone production — which naturally declines approximately 1% per year after age 30 — depends on adequate zinc, vitamin D, and magnesium. Prostate health, a concern for virtually every man over 50, is supported by selenium, lycopene, and zinc. Yet most men rely on generic multivitamins that fail to address these male-specific priorities.</p>

